---

Adjust racks to top and middle positions and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water and
@?salt{} to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender,
~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Return potatoes to #pot{} and cover to keep warm. (You'll finish the potatoes in Step 4.)

Place @bacon{4%ounce} on a #baking sheet{}; roast on top rack until crispy,
~{15-20%minutes}. Transfer to a #cutting board{}. Once cool enough to handle,
roughly chop.

Meanwhile, trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}(trimmed), separating whites from greens.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over high heat.
Add chicken and sear until golden brown, ~{2%minutes} per side. Turn off heat;
transfer chicken to one side of a second baking sheet. Wipe out pan and let
cool slightly.

Toss green beans on empty side of sheet with a drizzle of oil, salt, and pepper.
Roast on middle rack until chicken is cooked through and green beans are tender
and lightly browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

== Loaded Mashed Potatoes ==

To pot with potatoes, add @sour cream{1.5%tablespoon} and 2 TBSP
@butter{3%tablespoon}. Mash until smooth and creamy with a #potato masher{},
adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed.

Fold in half the bacon and half the scallion greens. Taste and season with salt and
pepper. Cover to keep warm.

> If bacon isn't finished yet, stir in right before serving.

== Cherry Pan Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for chicken over medium heat. Add scallion whites
and cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @water{1/4%cup}, @cherry jam{1%unit}, and @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}.
Cook, stirring, until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove from heat; stir in
remaining sour cream and 1 TBSP butter. Season with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Divide chicken, green beans, and mashed potatoes between plates. Spoon sauce over
chicken and sprinkle mashed potatoes with remaining bacon and remaining scallion
greens. Serve.